caption: One of my favorite restaurants in the area!! Amazing place! Wonderful food and great atmosphere! Very recommend ✨
The berry tea is perfect on a cold winter day. Love that you can add boba to any tea. Cute outdoor area with lots of seating.
I always love Teaism. Please consider going here for outside dining or carryout! Support this amazing local business. It has great healthy food, wonderful teas, and much more.
They make an good chai latte.
I enjoyed Teaism. I was able to order before arriving. Maria was cool and helpful.
I love the tea here! Great selection of drinks!
Never again. Incredibly rude service. Don’t believe the hype. Way way overrated. I’ve been here at least five times and it always disappoints.
Everything is delicious and the service is kind. They also have precautions in place so you can pick up your carry out safely during COVID times!
Like come on! This place is too good. It ain’t even fair.

Though I have not been to your (wonderful!) establishment (I pray I can make it to DC one day), yet I have received gifts of tea and other sweet things shipped to the West Coast from my beloved Sis Laura Grace (Donoghue).  We TOTALLY support you Michelle, et al., and especially during this time.  Blessings and all Love to you and yours! ❤️  And...THANK YOU for all you do, seen and unseen. 💞 Love from the other Washington, Patricia and John Ciminello

I like this restaurant! They prepare good meals, their menu is nice, The chief cook in that restaurant is well trained, I enjoy very much tasting all their dishes. The food is always tasty, the attitude towards the customers  is efficient. I visit often this place and I was never discontended. I recommend this place.
Awesome place to go relax or to go drink tea with some friends!!
Great food and delicious tea options.

Wonderful tea, and a quieter space. I like to go here with friends when we want to talk. Not many distractions, and they have good food options along with the tea.

(Vegan review) Creative dishes and very vegan friendly. Food was good but I'd probably try other dishes if I return. The curry lentil soup was very good and had a nice flavor to it. The black bean cake bento box was a lot colder than I expected overall. The black bean cake had a good flavor to, especially when paired with the rice and pickled onions) but I wasn't crazy about the sauce on the sweet potatoes (and I usually love sweet potatoes). The server strongly recommended the udon soup but I didn't feel like that at the time. I may consider it if I'm ever back in town. The tea (I had a lemon mint) was very delightful and simple syrup as well as sugar in the raw was available to sweeten.  It can get very crowded quite quickly and the layout makes that difficult to maneuver. Just be patient through the commotion. Seating is limited and tight on the first level but there appeared to be additional seating on a second level that I didn't venture to explore.
Courteous staff.  No waiting.

This review has nothing to do with the entire menu but for the bubble tea. I should have gone to a dedicated bubble tea place but instead I went here. The bubbles are not cooked correctly and the classic milk tea is watery.

Super cute place! There's some seating against the windows downstairs and some more tables upstairs but the place is pretty small! The lady at the counter is super welcoming and the general vibe of the place is quaint and comfy.  You order first then find somewhere to sit. If you go upstairs check back downstairs after a few minutes for your food!  Got the Salmon Chazuke - comes with a freshly brewed pot of (barley?) tea. The bowl portion is well seasoned and tasty with and without the tea :)  Also got the mango lassi which was more like a poorly blended mango smoothie. There were several ice chunks floating around but atleast it tasted like freshly ground mango. Disappointing but not displeased cuz it still tasted good, just don't expect a thick yogurty lassi!  Would love to come back and try other things on the menu!
Really disappointing. Not many vegan options and the one that I got was really bad; I didn't even end up finishing it. Won't go back.
Definitely a tea place, which means the food is not worth it.

i LOVE THIS PLACE! Their food is so refreshing and different in the best way possible. I've tried many of their meal items to include breakfast and lunch, it honestly never disappoints, also the people cooking the meals are the nicest ever, I've never had a bad experience here :)
Outstanding food, lovely setting, but so small! We had to move our table side to side to let diners on either side of us get out.

I cannot believe this restaurant’s quality. It is totally awesome!! The price is totally reasonable . Im from south korea and during staying in DC, this restaurant is the best asian cuisine ive had💕 thank you so much for your foods
Good food and great tea - nice quaint cafe

Teaism is such a treasure in Dupon! I am impressed by the variety of tea they serve and the ambiance. The decor is beauteaful, and it gave me the feeling of walking into a collage of Japanese and Chinese tea garden. The staff is extremely kind! It can get a bit crowded from time to time given its popularitea!
Interesting food menu – upstairs could be a cool, intimate date spot if not busy!
Cozy tea shop with great lunch menu.
Wonderful as always
Delightful, peaceful
Had a great lentil soup and salad. Will def come back

Great tea shop! I love their loose leaf selection, and their accessories are great gift ideas for the tea lovers in your life. Service has always been great there. I love their salted oatmeal cookies. And they have delicious foods, with a surprising selection (no, it's not just tea and baked goods... you can have apps and meals there too).
Perfect. Delicious food and tea
It's a great place to eat! We were there for breakfast and they have a very diverse menu with dishes from different countries. They also have gluten-free and other allergen-free options.
Excellent option for tea and food. The upstairs is quite lovely and the location feels very home like. Absolutely love coming here to chat and drink tea with friends.

This place has great ambiance downstairs. Upstairs smelled like bleach or some other cleaning product. It didn’t used to smell like that. Also I’ve ordered the udon soup for years and just recently they changed the noodles, which were the only reason I ordered this soup in the past. Now the noodles don’t seem homemade and are much thinner like soba noodles. Not worth the price tag.
Good spot for pan Asian lunch and tea
Love their ginger scones and curry dishes
Good all around fare great salty oats cookies.
Crowded and expensive but great food and ambiance.
Best Udon soup there is!

Pleasant, nice place to grab a meal or hang out. I had an iced chai tea which was delicious, and their tea collection in general seemed great. I had the okonomiyaki with a vegetable kabob for dinner and it was delicious! Freshly-made and very filling. There's not a ton of seating and some people take up a lot of space (and it also seemed like a lot of people come and stay for a while, doing work or chatting) but we were still able to find a table fairly quickly with a little patience. I would definitely come back!

My students ask to go to Teaism on a weekly basis, and each time, the atmosphere is welcoming. Whether you choose the warm ginger scones, the perfect chai, or the tea time offerings, I highly recommend you make a stop here!
Very nice tea shop. Cookies were good too!
One of my favorite places in DC. Phenomenal food with unique flavors and prep.
Love the tea selection, the food, and the energy. As a tea drinker it’s nice to have a place to go with such a vast selection, though I’m partial to the chai.

Really loved the atmosphere here - the upstairs seating area was a great spot to relax into and people watch cozily.  The teas we picked were perfect and a great late afternoon pick me up.  Really loved the broccoli tots - great texture, light on the inside and crispy on the outside. Flavor was very well balanced and not overpoweringly "green". The sauce it came with was very good.  And the jasmine creme brulee was absolutely delightful.

Worst bubble tea I’ve ever had in my life. Cashier tells me two min wait for my bubble tea to come out. People who ordered full meals after me got their order before I got my bubble tea...Da fuq. Finally get my bubble tea and I’m pretty sure the bubbles are stale. Not chewy at all, just a weird consistency that was not enjoyable at all. Go elsewhere for bubble tea

I love supporting operations that have vegan options. But I have to admit I was not impressed with the Our Dream Salad. Coming from a chef, it didn't seem freshly made.  The Coconut Miso on the other hand was very tasty. I would recommend this menu item.
Love their chai
Great food

I visit this place every time I am visiting my mom in DC. Very cozy place, aromatic teas and artsy crowd. I just have one advise: please tell your staff not to be so rude when working upstairs. They are throwing dishes so loud and disturb clients.
I go several times a week...love Teaism
Lovely spot with an amazing selection of teas. Went for breakfast, the cilantro eggs were a wonderful surprise. Of course, can't leave without a delicious ginger scone!
Solid choice! Awesome ambiance. This is the opposite of Starbucks in the best possible way.
Great tea, lovely little spot, cute upstairs and nice outdoor area out front
This place is the best. I strongly recommend Korean Brisket Sandwich and Thai Chicken Curry! This place definitely worth a visit. 10/10!

I walked in and the person at the desk didn't even greet me, she just waited or me to give my order. I had clearly never been in and needed some help with the menu, ordering process etc. I got the grilled chicken sandwich. I sat down and waited a long time before I realized that the food was ready and waiting for me up at the counter. I thought someone might bring it to me, and I wouldn't have minded getting it myself if I knew that was expected. It was yummy but the chicken was dry, and there wasn't enough mayo. I didn't quite feel like I got my moneys worth but maybe I have to try more items on the menu.
Going back for the chai alone.  The food, the service, the atmosphere.  All top notch, comfortable, easy going, and I love it.
Great for tea aficionados, and lovely, natural foods. Highly recommend the curry for its earthy flavors.
It is overrated. Food and interior is just under average. I tried taco, it was cold and you can get much better taco even in taco bell. Very limited space, dark and not clean!
Friendly staff and healthy but tasty food, not to mention a wide selection of teas! There’s a street view from the second floor.
Great bento boxes, I'd recommend the salmon variant.
Good veggie options!
Jazz music, perfect to work in your computer. Variety of flavorful natural and fresh tea. I ordered Today's Iced teasane: very good price and taste.
Best in the area. Great atmosphere, super friendly staff.
Tea
Fantastic scone, could not have asked for better. Wide vareity of tea with great descriptions to help you choose something new to try.

Wonderful food, just like the Penn Quarter location, but my goodness do they desperately need to clean the place! Dust is caked on the unsold bento boxes and other items on the merchandise shelf. The top of the stairwell against the wall as you head upstairs looks as though it has never been cleaned. I understand they're going for a particular rustic ambiance, but currently the place is just plain unkempt. I avoid giving negative reviews, but Teaism knows better and should really be doing better than this.
They have bubble tea and great cookies!
Amazing as always

Mehhh. Nothing special in my humble opinion. Overpriced.  Crowded.  Grungy.

I ordered some tea from here, a green tea that is sold at auction in china, and is fairly pricey, and when i got the tea, it was steeped in water that was too hot, for too long. Why offer nice tea if you are just going to ruin it? Dont come here if you care about tea, go to ching ching cha or a teavana, they do tea more justice.
Amazing tea, great food. The cooks are very friendly and really know what they're doing. I always go into a teaism when I see one!

Teaism is one of my favorite places to Nosh. Their bento boxes are full of tasty treats that can be customized to your pleasure. Their tea is good as well. Their chicken curry dish is a very good hot option and their coconut miso sipping broth keeps me coming back again and again. Seating is limited during a rush and it is hard to have a private conversation with people at all times.
Great little coffee/tea house for a break from playing tourist. Fantastic soups and treats, wonderful coffees and a nice selection of teas. We will definitely be back--enjoy!
Cozy and wonderful.
Lovely teas but crazy slow service
Cozy place for healthy meal or just a nice snack

I have to give this place four stars! Which is really great considering the fact that I believe this is a true brunch spot YET they do not serve mimosas! If they served the OJ with the champagne, I’d def give five. I had the organic curry chicken bowl for lunch and it was absolutely amazing. Filling. Flavorful. I enjoyed every bite. When I left, I tried the Earl Gray tea to go and it was also delicious! I was disappointed in the lack of seating and how close the seats are together, but I guess it gives it that homey and personal feel. I’m glad to have come across this place and will be back soon!

Definitely I don't recommend this place. It's so dark inside this place. Everything felt moldy and dirty. The walls paint is like a century ago. Food! I didn't like at all. Sandwich was horrible tasted so weird and was salty. Meat on it was dry dry ... i don't know how to describe it. I just really didn't like it. Definitely never going to try other things on menu specially with the attitude i recieved from manager. I ordered a drink beside my sandwich. I didn't realize it was full of ice and i was having my not delicious sandwich on the upper floor. I didn't want to leave my food to get cold to go back and change my cup of drink full of ice. So i finish my sandwich, i took the cup full of ice and i talked to employee which she called her manager. You imagine 2 /3 of cup was ice. By time i ate my sandwich and got to cashier 1/2 was ice because some of it was already melted. So i ask manager for refill, they refused. Ok. That is fine. And i said i want on half of cup to be refilled because i paid 3.50$ for this drink so more than half was ice. I don't say give me a full cup just give me half refill so it is what i paid for. Manager: "sorry, this drinks are homemade and expensive and I can't refill even half of the cup and you have to pay in full for another drink"! . I really didn't appreciate how they put their profits over customers satisfaction. Apparently they don't care. Well my advice to you dear reader, check that you don't pay for cup full of ice and you actually pay for the drink. I realized a bit late. It was my first time here. I very much regret it. . Also, the side of sandwiches you order, got no options except cucumbers that come in a small bowl with spicy sauce. I have never been to a place in my life that give only cucumbers as side of sandwich. I very much regret my visit here. Bad day, bad choice. You live and learn.
They use MSG in their food buyer beware !!!
Ummm...hell yeah.  This place has an ecletic menu and everything was great.  Wish i lived closer so i could frequent this spot.
Stops on line for 20 mins and after it didn't move gave up

delicious tea, warm atmosphere

Fantastically beautiful

Consistently excellent

Great selection of premium teas.  On a hot day the jasmine pearl tea, iced was just the right level of intensity of flavor while providing thirst quenching refreshment.  Loved the ginger scones with bits of candied ginger as well.
Kept up a high level of quality for two decades!
Great food and tea, especially love the selection of Tisane tea. Good seating upstairs.
Great spot! Love the atmosphere, and food!

This cafe offers some solid vegan options The Dream Salad, Vegan Cheeseburger, Curry Scramble, and vegan scones are among my favorites. The atmosphere can vary on the crowd this upstairs seating is tight and everyone doesn't have an indoor voice. There's free WiFi so it's a nice spot to chill with your device.

Get the ginger scones to start and then order anything else - you can’t go wrong! The tea is creative and refreshing and bento boxes are thoughtful and healthy. My personal favorites: cilantro scrambled eggs (even if you don’t like cilantro!) and udon noodle soup.

Used to go here when I was still working in the area. Had some lunch (chicken with potatoes and pickled cucumbers). It is always great to have a meal here and enjoy it with their expansive tea selection
Fantastic food and tea and the kind of ambiance and friendly  I'd expect to have in a crunchy college town, not Dupont circle-- such a refreshing surprise!
Want tea, they have it all. Cold drinks too and a great lunch menu, fairly priced for the location. Gets busy in the morning and lunch time weekdays. Friendly, expedient staff.

Great lunch spot.  We had the vegetable curry and chicken salad.  Both were excellent.  The staff was very friendly and helpful.  The service was great and our food came out pretty fast.  There is bar type seating on the lower main level and more tables upstairs.

Usually Teaism is the only place I trust to make decent tea (unless I make it myself). Very disappointed with both the incredibly weak chai and assam tea I ordered from Teaism today. More like tea-flavored water.  Yes, the restaurant was very busy, but please, if it takes a couple of minutes to brew a decent tea, then take the couple of minutes and do it right, no matter how busy you are. I'll wait. Sigh, I went home and made a strong black tea for myself.
The bubble tea is awesome The French toast will be the best you'll ever have
Had a bad experience but the owner was very gracious and Im also thinking about many of the good meals I had there
Loved the Miso Soup, many options for Vegans!  Quick service and cute atmosphere!
Kind of a strange layout, but good food and tea.
Cool Asian themed tea place with lots of options for tea and small Asian plates! Nice seating areas upstairs and on the first floor.

The service is good and the food arrives pretty quickly. I've tried everything from the vegan bento box to tea the dream salad to the tempeh scramble to what I'm posting pics of: avo/tomato combo, chopped salad and ginger scones. Great value for what I got, especially the ginger scones. I only expected one but got two. The description of the chopped salad and avocado is much more simple than what is actually served. Together the two appetizers mad a great lunch and the (vegan!) Ginger scones we're icing on top. I recommend downloading the 5 Stars app to get regular freebies.

If you’re coming here for good authentic bubble tea, you will be disappointed.  The thing tastes like sugar water milk with no tea flavor and very soggy bubbles. I managed to drink half of it and threw out the rest.  The food is OK, though a little overpriced for what you get.

Such a great place for bunch or just tea. They have a nice selection of both food and tea, including great bubble tea. There's not much room for a big group, but that makes it perfect for an intimate date or meeting with friends. They also have some nice sustainable practices, including a couple of menu items devoted to reducing food waste and a place to refill your water bottles.
Friendly staff. It’s located on a side street near Dupont. Only one bathroom on the first floor.

AMAZING! I wish I would give this place 10 stars. They stock a wide range of teas from White and Green to Oolong and Black. Great selection of vegetarian, vegan and gluten-free options that both veggie and meat lovers would enjoy.  For food, we order Vegan Cheeseburger, Okonomiyaki (savory scallion pancake) and a side of Broccoli Tots and for drinks, we ordered a Moroccan mint iced teas (unsweetened). Every bit and sip was superb! Excellent place to get away from the hustle and bustle of the city. This is a must for local and out of owners.
Nice atmosphere from outside, increasingly soulless inside.
Great place to have good tea and work a bit. But be warned:no place to plug your laptop
Love the family feel to it. The food is authentic and tastes great . Staff is super friendly

Staff was very helpful in explaining the food and the teas. I'm not a tea person but the tea was great. Vegan food options were delicious! Nice, casual atmosphere and interesting fellow patrons. The seating upstairs is tight but we didn't mind eavesdropping and then chatting a bit ;)
Salty Oat Cookie Korean beef Brisket Sandwich Chicken Sandwich
Have cilantro scrambled eggs with salmon for breakfast. I’m addicted to it.

There are tea houses & then there is Teaism. A superb array of teas perfectly brewed. The food menu has a large list of options for breakfast and lunch / dinner that changes seasonally. The menu is Asian inspired with soups, sandwiches, bentos, main dishes. I enjoy the majority of the offerings. Great Okonomiyaki, scrambled eggs with tea cured salmon, Korean brisket sandwich. Superb cookies, rice pudding and one of a kind jasmine creme brûlée. The DuPont location is my favorite. A very quaint place with limited seating but well worth the visit.

our tea was properly steeped and at the right temp. they steep the tea for you and do not let you keep the leaves for a second steeping. a 16oz pot of tea runs you around $5. many teas to choose from, all high quality.
Nice selection of teas. The stuff to eat is just ok.
Came here with a friend and shared great Asian fusion food over an intimate conversation. Very casual and cozy atmosphere. Great tea

I used to hang out at this place all the time, and just went back for the first time in ages. Quality product and helpful staff, but the place could seriously use a deep clean. I know they're going for a "rustic" teahouse vibe, but it's starting to shade into "shabby."
I went there again! So creative concept and great vegetarian options. Additionally, tea lovers - must try!
Great Tea and a relaxing atmosphere.
Delicious! Worth stopping in for a snack or a whole meal. Vegan options with some adjustments.

I love to go here for any meal. If fragrance is your favorite aspect of flavor, you will too. Plus they have real actual from-a-tree maple syrup for their french toast! I have found several new favorite tea varieties here.

A lovely spot for all forms of actual tea and a few tisanes. Enjoyed a golden needle with fresh ginger on a rainy day. Helpful and patient staff. Great gluten free cookie. Looked like they have lovely lunches too.
A very large selection of teas and unique lunch menu. I like the Star of Africa tea and the tacos.

This is one of my favorite places in DC I love the cozy atmosphere the fantastic food the fact that my friend can get a cup of tea and I can eat a Korean brisket sandwich and we can catch up for a few hours

Had a lovely lunch at the Dupont Teaism with a friend recently. I've been to this location multiple times and always have a wonderful experience. The pancakes I got this time were amazing - tasted like something my grandparents would have made for me at home! And the bubble tea was, of course, great too.
Incredible collection of teas. Good food for lunch or takeout as well.
Great place but I wish there was more seating for patrons.
Great location, friendly staff, awesome Tea selection, and comfortable space to relax and enjoy drink and conversation—top notch!
Chai and organic coconut curry 🥘 are delicious 😋.

Some of the other reviews say that this place is expensive. That may be true but my god this place is fantastic. I tried the bubble tea and the mochi? I absolutely loved them. The Mochi was my absolute favorite.

The food is expensive and there aren't waitress... I ordered Salmon Tacos and a Ginger Limonade... THE TACOS WERE SPICY AS HELL ( DOESN'T SAY SO IN THE MENU) AND THE LIMONADE IS 1/2 ICE (+really small). The chicken curry was just ok, but it didnt have much flavor to be honest. The mango juice (like the limonade) was 1/2 ice. Overall disapointing and expensive 2/10
long waits but still worth it
Classic tea shop with great services.
Comfort, delicious food and they have a koi pond. Need I say more?
Great tea, quiet atmosphere. There is WiFi but no outlets so you can't stay super long to work on a laptop which is ideal.

You wrote a review for Teaism Dupont Circle 5 days ago 5.0 star rating 1/4/2018 It's a cute little tea shop with many food options. The first floor only has a few seats along the window and a few more small tables upstairs. You need to serve yourself. I like the decor of the place, very cozy and interesting.  They have a chart of all their items about if it's vegan, gluten free, or whatever you need to know. Ask them for the chart if you need.  They are also very flexible about what you want to put in your food or not want to put in. Don't shy about making the request.  We ordered the black bean cake bento and udon noddle with vegetables. Both were very delightful! The udon noddle has a sour broth, kind of unusual but I like it. Such a great choice on a cold winter night. The Black bean cake bento is full of surprises! My favorite item in there is actually the rice. I know, brown rice just sounds boring, but they seasoned it so well. It for sure not the ordinary brown rice you are thinking about. The black bean cake with coconut is very delicious too.
Such a cozy place with exceptional food and tea. Amazing selection of fine teas.
The best tea and food place in Dupont

I have loved Teaism since forever. They don't have a huge menu, but everything is always good, and the people who work there know their stuff, including the tea. The menu also changes over time, which I love. There are always wonderful vegetarian options. The only downside, which you can't blame them for, is how popular it is and frequently it is hard to find a seat to enjoy it.
Great local place for Asian fusion food. Especially like the tea selection

Ordered an iced tea. Tasted like water, no option to have sweet either. Online menu advertised miso soup, drove over here and all the offered was some coconut broth "miso". The cashier said it tastes very good, it was gross. Also over salted. The main reason we drove here was for the bubble tea, very disappointing. It was very chewy boba and we called in advance before here and asked if they had mango bubble tea, they said yes. When we arrived they said they have mango juice to which they can add Boba .... Seriously? Even Brown rice was bad.  Stay AWAY!!!!!

amazing tea selection, awesome chai, cozy vibe 😊
Friendly staff and delicious food... Everything I expect from Teaism.
I had a bento. It was delicious.
The udon noodle soup here is unreal. There’s something magical in that broth and the noodles are chewy and toothsome. Their salty oak cookies are also addictive.

Milk tea!
Favorite place for lunch, but does get crowded. Love that they don't use plastic bags and are trying to phase out plastic straws.
Incredible experience and atmosphere will be here weekly even tho I don't live in the area. 10/10 service
So many intriguing options!

I love stopping at Teaism (bentos are great, salty oat cookies are so dense, and the chai is spicy) but today I tried their pearl tea. I should've said something, maybe something was actually off. The pearls are hard like toffee. Or Now N Later candies. The milk tea is nice but too sweet for me (maybe you can request no sugar). I also noticed that I had much fewer pearls than someone else's order that came out at the same time. I would've been more annoyed about that if they were a perfect soft texture!

Love this place, has a great vibe to it. The second floor has a nice view. The food is very tasty and, ofcourse their teas are great. The bubble tea is especially really good

This is a public place with food & drinks, not a school library. I realize this isn't the owner's fault, but thought I'd shared in case anyone's looking for an uber-quiet place?

This is more like a fast food place. You order at the counter wait a bit and get your food either to take out or eat in. There's limited seating downstairs, so if you choose to eat in you have to negotiate a flight of stairs to find a table. This being said, the food is worth it. Vegan friendly.
My favorite. The upstairs is charming with a lovely view of the neighborhood outside. It can be crowded. But it's worth the wait for those delicious Japanese cabbage pancakes.
Vegetarian sandwich and tea were both great
Awesome food and tea
Nice tea and loved their chicken bento
great place of relaxation

Great food, great tea. Small complaints/things to keep in mind: there is not much seating, it's expensive, there is no real parking so it's best to come by Metro and walk over, and you order downstairs then have to stand around waiting for your order before you can go sit. If you go sit thinking someone will call your number from downstairs, you will never get your food. I would recommend bringing at least 1 friend to scout out a table somewhere and hold it for you while you go get the tea/food order for you guys. Still worth it. I want to go back. Yum!
Nice little tea shop with 2 levels. Tea variety is out of this world and definitely creates a tranquil environment. They do offer free hot water refills. Street parking outside.
Fantastic, cozy tea house. Staff is always warm, welcoming, and helpful.
I love it here so much. Such good, healthy food. Delicious drinks, cool atmosphere. It's a bit pricey for cafe food, worth it but if you are on a strict budget- maybe not.
Tasty creative food.  Amazing tea selection.  Great decor and friendly staff.  They carry my favorite cookies, Salty Oats.  I get the cookies every time I come to DC

This is a great place, the food and drinks are delicious and the decor is amazing. Only drawback is there's not a lot of tables so it's not uncommon to wait standing for people to leave.
Trendy and elegant.
One of my favorite places in the city. They have a great chai and bubble tea, and their food is unique, delicious, and not too heavy. The ambiance is fantastic too.
Food is fantastic. Seating is limited.
Tempeh scramble isn't really a scrambled, just stewed in curry sauce. Everything else was delicious, especially the French toast!
Really unique great food.

This is a cute tea cafe near Dupont circle. They have a delicious selection of cold/hot teas and some snacks as well. I didn't see any outlets for computers, but if you make sure your things are charged well beforehand, you can enjoy sitting upstairs and doing some work.
Fun little tea shop with lots of cute tea sets when i lived nearby.

This is a lovely little tea house. Everything I've had here has been delicious (and I've been coming here regularly for a couple years.) If you're here, their matcha iced tea is delicious and refreshing, and their ginger scones are just amaaazzzing. As well, their bentos are good as are their scrambled eggs with smoked salmon.

It is the best scrambled eggs ever with ginger and cilantro 💕  It warmed me inside out (22 degrees out).  The people here are super friendly.  It feels clean and satisfied after the meal.  Thank you❣️
Delicious food and quick service. They do tea great obviously but have lots of other options.

Prefer the Teaism in Penn Quarter. The DuPont Circle location is small, crowded, has poor traffic flow, difficult steps to its upstairs dining room, and the food took a long time to arrive. But it's a very popular place and is charming in its own way.  I wouldn't avoid it, but I also wouldn't go out of my way for it.
